pageContext.claim: “The FBI, as you know, is all over talking to everybody, and I would expect -- he's a very high quality person -- I would expect it's going to turn out very well for the judge. … Yeah, they have free rein. They're going to do whatever they have to do, whatever it is they do.”
pageContext.analysis: The White House limited the scope of the FBI's investigation into Christine Blasey Ford's account of being sexually assaulted by Brett Kavanaugh in 1982. Neither Ford nor Kavanaugh, Trump's Supreme Court nominee at the time, were questioned about the incident.
